The article discusses the passing of Ruth Bader Ginsburg, an Associate Justice of the Supreme Court of the United States, and her impact on the country. Ginsburg served on the Supreme Court for over 27 years and was known for her powerful dissents. She fought for equality for women and secured rights for the disabled. Despite battling cancer, Ginsburg continued to serve on the Court and inspired many with her commitment to the law. As a mark of respect, the article states that the flag of the United States will be flown at half-staff.